        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 7:11PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Funston, or over Anson, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Anson, Merkel, Hawley, Lueders, Trent, Noodle, Nugent, Avoca,
Funston, Lake Fort Phantom Hill, The Intersection Of Us-
180 And Farm Road 600, Hodges, Big Country Baptist Assembly, Truby,
and Stith.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 262 and 275.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
